  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, I'm Miss Maya. I like watching football matches that are close to home, how’s your exam prep going after the last chat?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Miss Maya, exams are stressful, but I try my best. I like watching football too, especially when my team is playing. Last night's match was very close, but I couldn't sleep well after. How about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that,  close matches and exams both keep you up. Did you stay up to see the final result?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I stayed up late to watch the match end. It was 2-2 in the end, very exciting. But I feel very kheyal tosh today, couldn’t get back to sleep. How was your day? Did you watch any match recently?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You stayed up for the full match, that’s dedication! \"Kheyal tosh\" sounds like a local expression — I’d love to hear more about it. How did you feel when the score ended 2-2?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Actually, \"kheyal tosh\" is a Bengali phrase meaning \"without energy\" or \"tired out.\" I feel like a zombie today. The match was so tight—I was cheering for my team the whole time. When it ended 2-2, I was happy but also sad because we didn’t win. How about you, did you ever stay up for a football match?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You explained it perfectly — I get that mix of happiness and sadness when a match ends in a draw. Staying up for football is totally worth it, even if you feel like a zombie the next day. Did you catch any other exciting matches recently?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, there was another match yesterday, but I didn't watch it. I was too tired and wanted to sleep. My team plays again tomorrow, maybe I will try to watch that. Do you like football?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, and I get the priority of rest — football can wait when you're tired. Your team has a match tomorrow, right? I like football, especially when there's that electric feeling of a close game. What team are you cheering for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm cheering for Mohun Bagan, they are my favorite team. I feel proud when they play well. The electric feeling you said — I know exactly what you mean. Even if it's a draw, the excitement is real. But today I'm too kheyal tosh to feel much. Let's talk about something else. How was your day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said Mohun Bagan is your pride — that makes sense. I get how a draw still holds that buzz. Being kheyal tosh sounds heavy. How has your day been so far?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My day was okay, but I’m tired too, maybe because of work. I didn’t get much done today. I was thinking about watching a Bengali movie, but I don’t have energy. Maybe tomorrow. How do you relax after a long day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You didn’t get much done — I get that, work and tired days don’t mix well. Bengali movies are a nice idea, but rest is better when you’re low on energy. How do you usually unwind when you feel this tired?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "When I feel too tired, I just lie down and watch some football highlights. It makes me feel better, even if I can’t watch the full match. Sometimes I also listen to music or just take a short nap. But today, even thinking feels hard. I think I’ll just rest for now. Thanks for talking, Miss Maya. Gotta go. Talk to you soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Rest is the best plan when even thinking feels heavy, take it easy, Rohan. Football highlights are a smart pick, they’re like little energy boosts. Talk to you soon!"
    }
  ],
